        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:13PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 213 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near Lynchburg,
moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail may cause minor damage to
vegetation.

Locations impacted include...
Leesburg, New Vienna, East Monroe, Samantha, New Antioch, Lynchburg,
Sabina, Russell, Lees Creek, Midland, Reesville, Martinsville,
Morrisville, and Highland.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM EDT for
central and southwestern Ohio. A Severe Thunderstorm Watch also
remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for south central Ohio.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
